Description: Fragment of oval handle with a gradual curve from a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pink-brown; dark inclusions. Circular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and grape cluster or worn rose symbol. Sampled for NAA and thin section.
Curator's comments: Name Armosilas. Trimmed. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.31,42. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0922.22.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0690)
